        "content": "<p>After learning about proof by <code>contradiction</code> in MoP, I set myself the following challenge: </p>\n<p><strong>Show there is no smallest positive rational number.</strong></p>\n<p>I formulated it as disproving the following:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>:</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\exists r \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+, \\forall s \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+: r \\le s.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0158em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.988em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>that is, proving</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">¬</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>:</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\neg \\exists r \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+, \\forall s \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+ :  r \\le s</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬∃</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0158em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.988em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>which is equivalent to</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">¬</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>:</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall r \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+, \\neg \\forall s \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+ :  r \\le s</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0158em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.988em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>which in turn is equivalent to</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">¬</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall r \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+, \\exists s \\in \\mathbb{Q}^+ :  \\neg r \\le s</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0158em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.988em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>(I think the above is correct)</p>\n<hr>\n<p>I'm struggling with converting this into Lean. My code thus far has 2 problems I'd like advice on:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- &lt; -- problem 1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ring</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- &lt; -- problem 2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Code Problems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>How do I change the set ℚ to ℚ+? I tried asserting hypotheses as follows, but this fails: <code>example (h1: r &gt; 0) (h2: s &gt; 0): ∀ r : ℚ, ∃ s : ℚ, ¬ r ≤ s := by</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>How do I create an intermediate result that <code>r ≥ r/2</code>? The <code>ring</code> and <code>linarith</code> tactics don't do it. It feels like a trivial result that should require lots of code to prove.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 488938272,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1734133014
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>How do I change the set ℚ to ℚ+</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>\\forall r : \\Q, r &gt; 0 -&gt; \\exists s : \\Q, s &gt; 0 \\and \\not r \\leq s</code></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>How do I create an intermediate result that <code>r ≥ r/2</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>have foo : r \\geq r / 2</code></p>",
        "id": 488938488,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1734133160
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>take a look at <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=half_le_self#doc\">docs#half_le_self</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=half_lt_self#doc\">docs#half_lt_self</a></p>",
        "id": 488940170,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1734134317
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>here's one approach:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℚ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gt_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gt_zero</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">half_lt_self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 488940883,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1734134681
